1 Section 3. KRS 18A.115 is amended to read as follows:
2 (1) The classified service to which KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200 shall apply shall comprise
3 all positions in the state service now existing or hereafter established, except the
4 following:
5 (a) The General Assembly and employees of the General Assembly, including the
6 employees of the Legislative Research Commission;
7 (b) Officers elected by popular vote and persons appointed to fill vacancies in
8 elective offices;
9 (c) Members of boards and commissions;
10 (d) Officers and employees on the staff of the Governor, the Lieutenant
11 Governor, the Office of the Secretary of the Governor's Cabinet, and the
12 Office of Program Administration;
13 (e) Cabinet secretaries, commissioners, office heads, and the administrative heads
14 of all boards and commissions, including the executive director of Kentucky
15 Educational Television;
16 (f) Employees of Kentucky Educational Television who have been determined to
17 be exempt from classified service by the Kentucky Authority for Educational
18 Television, which shall have sole authority over such exempt employees for
19 employment, dismissal, and setting of compensation, up to the maximum
20 established for the executive director and his or her principal assistants;
21 (g) One (1) principal assistant or deputy for each person exempted under
22 subsection (1)(e) of this section;
23 (h) One (1) additional principal assistant or deputy as may be necessary for
24 making and carrying out policy for each person exempted under subsection
25 (1)(e) of this section in those instances in which the nature of the functions,
26 size, or complexity of the unit involved are such that the secretary approves
27 such an addition on petition of the relevant cabinet secretary or department
